      <title>Sounds Jewish: Passover special, April 2011 - podcast</title>
      <link>http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/belief/audio/2011/apr/18/sounds-jewish-april-passover-special</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Join comedian and performer &lt;a href="http://daveschneider.co.uk"&gt;David Schneider&lt;/a&gt;, standing in for Jason Solomons this month, for a Passover special. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Think of it as the Jewish Christmas – the one night of the year when it's all but compulsory for Jewish families to sit together around a table laden with food. But the seder night is not all about eating and barely-suppressed tension with your relatives: it kicks off the eight-day festival that marks what is the defining experience of the Jewish people – the escape from slavery in Egypt. A combination of songs, prayers, readings and symbolic nibbles, conducted in people's homes, the seder is like nothing else.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;David talks to actor Maureen Lipman, playwright &lt;a href="http://www.thejc.com/arts/theatre/47572/interview-amy-rosenthal"&gt;Amy Rosenthal&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="http://www.newlondon.org.uk/"&gt;Rabbi Jeremy Gordon&lt;/a&gt;  and others as they gather at &lt;a href="http://www.tricycle.co.uk/current-programme-pages/special-events/the-other-seder/"&gt;The Other Seder&lt;/a&gt;, an evening of theatre organised by the Jewish Community Centre for London, showcasing four new short plays inspired by aspects of the seder's central theme: freedom. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;He hears how egg-and-saltwater is one of Maureen's favourite dishes, how the seder reveals how truly right-on you are and why matzah should carry a health warning ...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sounds Jewish is produced by the &lt;a href="http://jewishcommunitycentre.org.uk"&gt;Jewish Community Centre for London&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;• Find us on &lt;a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/JCC-Sounds-Jewish-Podcast-in-association%20-with-The-Guardian/22149462397"&gt;Facebook&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="http://twitter.com/Sounds_Jewish"&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p style="clear:both" /&gt;</description>
